headline: indiGOtech Closes Strategic Funding Round from Industry Giants to Accelerate Sustainable Ride Hail and Delivery for Communities
summary: indiGOtech (Tradename: GO), a new mobility tech company based in Massachusetts, today announced it closed a $54 million Series BB funding round, including investments from FedEx (NYSE: FDX), Foxconn (2354.TW) and FM Capital. These investments accelerate GO's mission to provide sustainable local transport, leveraging its patented SmartWheels™, Smart EVs and Smart Mobility Services.
